<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>6. EDM</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">The Electronic Distance Meter (EDM) measures the distance between fixed benchmarks on volcanic flanks. The instrument both sends and receives electromagnetic signals. Short-range EDM&#8217;s typically measure distances of less than 10 km, have an accuracy of 5 mm, and use the near visible infrared part of the spectrum for measuring distances. Medium-range EDM&#8217;s often measure distances of less than 50 km. Depending on the distance between the EDM and reflector, the wavelength of the returned signal will be out of phase with the transmitted signal. The instrument compares the phase of the transmitted and received signals and measures the phase difference electronically to calculate distance.</p>
